subSubSection.paragraph:
Male.
(
Figs 21–22
). Similar to female in structure and coloration, except body 7.0–10.0 mm; lower face 1.0– 1.2× as broad as high (from supraclypeal suture to base of antenna); head, in dorsal view, with margin of the gena flat behind the eyes; margin of the gena 0.5–0.6× length of eye, in dorsal view; posterior ocelli separated from eyes by 0.4–0.6× its diameter in dorsal view; fore wing 6.0–7.0 mm; tergite I 1.2–1.5× as long as posteriorly broad; tergite II 1.4–1.5× as long as posteriorly broad; tergite III 1.2–1.4× as long as posteriorly broad; sternite IX (
Fig 24
) longer than high, with lateral and anterior margins strongly sclerotised, lateral margin flat and posterior margin slightly concave centrally, with few bristles widely spaced posteriorly. Genital capsule (
Figs 25–26
): Paramere truncated apically, slightly narrower than the parameral lamina, with bristles except in posterior margin; volsellar lamina with spaced bristles laterally and apically on the central region and with a set of four to five bristles in anterolateral region, just below the base of the digitus; cuspis robust with about five to six teeth aligned in the mid part until apex and with some small bristles in basal region and about five small bristles spaced laterally in apical region; digitus with teeth on apex, rounded distally and angular ventrally, with the margins of the apical region narrower than base; aedeagus with few teeth on apex and its apex slightly curved downward in lateral view.
